Earth except for the toughest micro-organisms.<br>
500,000,000 years after that the sun will blow up,<br>
and its remains will collapse into a white dwarf star.<br>
2.The growth of the sun into a red giant will heat <br>
up mars, release its frozen water, and atmosphere<br>
during the last eons of the suns life.This will turn mars<br>
into an earth like planet for up to the next <br>
 500,000,000 years or so after the event.<br>
3. Just colonizing Mars, and colonizing the outer solar system is  enough potentially to keep the human race alive in this<br>
solar system for the next 1,000,000,000 years or so.<br>
4. This means that we have enough time to reach the stars,<br>
and to colonize them even with nothing but chemical rocketry,<br>
and solar sails for propulsion..By means of a (sun burn) trajectory, we can leave the solar system via a solar<br>
gravity boost by flying close behind the sun  on a solar gravity whip trajectory. In this way even a chemical rocket  would be thrown out of the solar system  by the suns gravity at up to 300 kilometers/sec which is 670,000 miles per hour.<br>
5.  Then the suns velocity around the galaxy of 481,000<br>
miles per hour could be added to this to provide a velocity<br>
of about  1,100,000 miles per hour in interstellar space.<br>
6. This is 1/700th of light speed which is enough to reach<br>
the nearest stars in about 3100 years. This is a long time<br>
by human standards ,but for a Multigenerational Noahs Ark<br>
, type 3 star mission this will work.<br>
7. By using a combination  of solar sail propulsion,Solar electric propulsion and a sun burn type gravity whip trajectory we could launch a solar propelled interstellar ark out of the solar system at about, 1/90th of light speed which is .011 c. This will get you to the nearest stars in about<br>
400 years. This will work for a  type 2 Multigenerational<br>
interstellar space ark.A nuclear fission powered electric ion or plasma drive rocket  can also achieve about .01 C on a star mission.<br>
 8. By  using Orion or Deadalas class thermonuclear pulse<br>
rockets we can launch a star mission at somewhere <br>
between 0.08 C , and .15 C (8% to 15 % of light velocity)<br>
This will enable an interstellar ark to reach the nearest stars<br>
in not more then 40 to 50 years flight time on a type 1 star mission. <br>
9. If we want to go faster then .10 C to the stars ,then  some version of the interstellar ramjet or  Rair, a Maser electric  propulsion system , OR a matter-antimatter annhilation powered propulsion propulsion system<br>
will probably  be required.<br>
10. All these facts means that the human race will survive<br>
logn enough to see the end of the sun, and maybe even<br>
the end of time , unless it destroys itself in some nuclear,<br>
biological, chemical, and pyrotechnic war war 3  of<br>
 armageddon- apocalypse in some idiotic, religous<br>
war, or war  of imperialism between would be empire<br>
 builders on  earth. So lomg as we have settled at least one other planet before a war of armageddon we can survive<br>
